<taxonomicNameLabel box="[635,699,1206,1229]" pageId="20" pageNumber="360" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[159,762,703,1556]" pageId="20" pageNumber="360">
Remarks — The only known axonopsine genus with more than three or four pairs of acetabula is 
<taxonomicName authority="Smit and Pesi'c, 2010" authorityName="Smit" authorityYear="2010" box="[188,625,1321,1346]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Omanaxonopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="20" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[188,361,1322,1345]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="360">Omanaxonopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smit H. &amp; Pesi'c V." box="[371,625,1321,1346]" pageId="20" pageNumber="360" pagination="151 - 195" refId="ref9572" refString="Smit H., Pesi'c V. 2010 - New species of water mites from Oman, with some zoogeographical notes (Acari: Hydrachnidia) - Acarologia 50 (2): 151 - 195." type="journal article" year="2010">Smit and Peši´c, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this genus has one pair of glandularia between the fourth leg sockets and the genital field, has no dorsal glandularia flanking the excretory pore, has a truncate lateral projection of the ventral shield and leg claws with dorsal and ventral clawlets (
<bibRefCitation author="Smit H. &amp; Pesi'c V." pageId="20" pageNumber="360" pagination="151 - 195" refId="ref9572" refString="Smit H., Pesi'c V. 2010 - New species of water mites from Oman, with some zoogeographical notes (Acari: Hydrachnidia) - Acarologia 50 (2): 151 - 195." type="journal article" year="2010">Smit and Peši´c 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
